## Ensuring good skin contact
For flat reference electrodes, it can be a good idea to connect the electrode directly to the clip, and tuck it under the cap. This is particularly true if you choose to place the electrode at the mastoid.

For brush electrodes, be sure that the pins reach the scalp through the hair. Pinch the clip, and wiggle it around (side to side, or in circular motion) until the bristles have found their way through the hair and are touching the scalp. Subjects should not feel discomfort at any point. 
